subject: Re: [junit] help
msgSnippet: As for books, I have loved both JUnit in Action by Vincent Massol and Ted Husted, and JUnit Recipes: Practical Methods for Programmer Testing by J. B.
messageBody:
As for books, I have loved both JUnit in Action by Vincent Massol and
Ted Husted, and JUnit Recipes: Practical Methods for Programmer
Testing
by J. B. Rainsberger. Next on my list is Pragmatic Unit Testing in
Java with JUnit
by Andy Hunt and Dave Thomas. Pick any one (or all) of these and I
think you will get started just fine! :)


Bent
